        <briefdescription>
<para>This functions runs a self-test on the driver and hardware device. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This self test performs a local loopback and verifies data can be sent and received.</para><para>The statistics are cleared at the end of the test. The time for this test to execute is proportional to the baud rate that has been set prior to calling this function.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_uart_ns550" kindref="compound">XUartNs550</ref> instance.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><verbatim>            - XST_SUCCESS if the test was successful
            - XST_UART_TEST_FAIL if the test failed looping back the data
</verbatim></para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This function can hang if the hardware is not functioning properly. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
